[normal]ANNEX A[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Response by the British Geological Survey to the [bold]Business, Innovation and Skills Committee Select Committee Announcement No.11 – [bold]EXTRACTIVE INDUSTRIES INQUIRY[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Background to the British Geological Survey[bold]The British Geological Survey is a part of the Natural Environment Research Council (
[normal]NERC
[normal]) and is its principal supplier of national capability in 
[normal]geoscience
[normal]. It advances understanding of the structure, properties and processes of the solid Earth system through interdisciplinary surveys, monitoring and research for the benefit of society. The BGS is the UK's premier provider of objective and authoritative 
[normal]geoscientific
[normal] data, information and knowledge for wealth creation, sustainable use of natural resources, reducing risk and living with the impacts of environmental change. 
[normal]We are a world-leading 
[normal]geoscience
[normal] centre for:
[normal]MineralsUK
[normal] is the 
[normal]British Geological Survey (BGS)
[normal] Centre for Sustainable Mineral Development. Facilitated by the BGS Minerals and Waste science programme, the Centre is a global leader in the compilation, provision and analysis of mineral statistics and the major UK national provider of spatial and statistical minerals information. We also carry out research in areas directly relevant to our user community, such as 
[normal]metallogenesis
[normal], land-use impacts of mineral extraction and 
[normal]geomaterials
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
